  "prompt": "Can I keep savings account if my status changes to NRI? What happens to my PPF and NPS accounts?",
  "response": "Here's what happens to your accounts when you become an NRI:\n\nSavings Account:\n- Can convert existing account to NRO (Non-Resident Ordinary) account\n- Can operate the account normally\n- Funds can be repatriated with certain restrictions\n- Earn regular interest rates\n\nPPF (Public Provident Fund):\n- Cannot make fresh contributions after becoming NRI\n- Existing account can continue until maturity\n- Cannot extend the account beyond 15 years\n- Can be closed prematurely with penalty\n\nNPS (National Pension System):\n- Can continue the account\n- Can contribute from abroad\n- Can withdraw/transfer as per NPS rules\n- Tax implications might change\n\nRecommendations:\n- Inform your bank about NRI status\n- Convert savings account to NRO/NRE\n- Consult tax advisor for specific guidance\n- Keep KYC documents updated\n- Check repatriation rules\n\nImportant: Specific rules can vary, so always verify current regulations with your bank and financial institutions.",
